contact.contactName: Toronto and East York Community Council

noticeDescription: Take notice that the Council of the City of Toronto has passed By-law 571-2022 to designate the property at 78 Ontario Street (including the convenience address at 82 Ontario Street) and 90 Ontario Street and 410 Richmond Street East (Ward 13 Toronto Centre) as being of cultural heritage value or interest.
subheading: In the Matter of the Ontario Heritage Act R.S.O. 1990 Chapter 0.18 and City of Toronto, Province of Ontario
title: Notice of Passing of By-Law - 78 Ontario Street, 90 Ontario Street and 410 Richmond Street East
topics: Heritage > Intention to designate a heritage property
